ZAAIPLAAS police outside Groblersdal in Mpumalanga arrested a 30-year-old man for the alleged murder of his neighbour just minutes after the crime was committed. According to police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe, the incident happened at about 7am on Tuesday. &ldquo;It is alleged that a passer-by found the suspect attacking the 39-year-old female victim. &ldquo;He chopped the female to death with an axe and then sucked the blood from her dead body,&rdquo; said Ngoepe. He said police were alerted and reacted to the attack immediately. &ldquo;The suspect was arrested at the crime scene. &ldquo;He still had the axe in his hands at the time of the arrest.&rdquo; Ngoepe said the man will appear in the Zaaiplaas Magistrates Court soon. &ldquo;An investigation is under way to determine what happened.&rdquo; &ndash; NEWS24